When compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[597,714,869,894]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[597,714,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[731,846,869,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1789]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Lygephila sp., adults. 1, L. stueningi, male, holotype, China; 2, 3, ditto, female, paratype; China; 4, ditto, male paratype, China; 5, 6, L. ludicra, Russia, Tuva, female and male; 7, L. longicoecum, male, holotype, China; 8, L. maxima, male, Russia, Khabarovsk." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184113/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Figs. 
<number box="[799,846,869,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[860,935,869,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="14.18">
<figureCitation box="[860,891,869,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,355,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1424,355,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Lygephila sp., male genitalia. 13, L. stueningi, male, paratype, genit. prep. 5882 M. Fibiger; 14, L. ludicra, Turkey, genit. prep. 3561 M. Fibiger; 15, L. longicoecum, holotype, China, ZFMK genit. prep. 2019 V. Kononenko; 16, L. maxima, South Korea, CIS genit. prep. 169 - 1 Han H. L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184115/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[905,935,869,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,269,961,985]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,156,900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1405,156,915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lygephila sp., female genitalia. 17, L. stueningi, paratype, genit. prep. 5883 M. Fibiger; 18, L. ludicra, Mongolia, genit. prep. C 21 B. Goater; 19, L. maxima, Russian Far East, Primorye Territory, genit. prep. 5725 M. Fibiger; 20, L. longicoecum, paratype, China, IBSS genit. prep. 698 V. Kononenko." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">18</figureCitation>
</number>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[952,1091,869,894]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stueningi">
<emphasis box="[952,1091,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. stueningi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the broader wings, and most markedly by the interstigmal, longitudinal black streak inwardly from the lower part of the reniform stigma. In the male genitalia it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[785,901,949,974]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[785,901,949,974]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[919,1005,949,975]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1415,355,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1424,355,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Lygephila sp., male genitalia. 13, L. stueningi, male, paratype, genit. prep. 5882 M. Fibiger; 14, L. ludicra, Turkey, genit. prep. 3561 M. Fibiger; 15, L. longicoecum, holotype, China, ZFMK genit. prep. 2019 V. Kononenko; 16, L. maxima, South Korea, CIS genit. prep. 169 - 1 Han H. L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184115/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[975,1005,949,975]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
) by the relatively shorter uncus; the relatively broader valva, the more distal harpe; and by the very different shape of the everted vesica; in the female genitalia it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[528,645,1029,1054]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[528,645,1029,1054]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[664,751,1029,1055]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,269,961,985]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,156,900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1405,156,915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lygephila sp., female genitalia. 17, L. stueningi, paratype, genit. prep. 5883 M. Fibiger; 18, L. ludicra, Mongolia, genit. prep. C 21 B. Goater; 19, L. maxima, Russian Far East, Primorye Territory, genit. prep. 5725 M. Fibiger; 20, L. longicoecum, paratype, China, IBSS genit. prep. 698 V. Kononenko." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[721,751,1029,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) by the much shorter, heavily sclerotised antrum and the super-elliptic shape of corpus bursae; that of 
<taxonomicName box="[678,793,1069,1094]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[678,793,1069,1094]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is elongate, broadest posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,549,1815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1109,1135]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">Description.</emphasis>
Imago (
<figureCitation box="[455,565,1109,1135]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,194,1789]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Lygephila sp., adults. 1, L. stueningi, male, holotype, China; 2, 3, ditto, female, paratype; China; 4, ditto, male paratype, China; 5, 6, L. ludicra, Russia, Tuva, female and male; 7, L. longicoecum, male, holotype, China; 8, L. maxima, male, Russia, Khabarovsk." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184113/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Figs 
<number box="[518,565,1109,1135]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[719,854,1109,1135]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="44.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="42.0">42–47 mm</quantity>
. Thorax and ground colour of forewing grayish brown, powdered densely with dark brown scales, including fringes; all cross-lines present, generally well marked, though postmedial line is absent in some specimens; postmedial area by costa dark brown; terminal line indicated by small, black intervenal dots; reniform stigma dark brown, with prominent black spots; orbicular stigma marked by blackish spot; prominent interstigmatal streak presents from ventral edge of reniform stigma. Hindwing light grey-brown, distally with a broad, blackish brown band; first half of fringes light brown, outwardly whitish. Underside of forewing and costal part of hindwing brown, lower part of hindwing light grey; without lines and discal spots. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[639,936,1389,1415]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[833,921,1389,1415]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1380,1404]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,474,1321]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,474,1321]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Apopestes sp., adults. 9, A. curiosa, male, holotype, China; 10, A. spectrum, male, Dalmatia; 11, A. phantasma, male, Turkmenia, Kopet-Dagh; 12, A. indica, male, China, Li-kiang." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184114/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[890,921,1389,1415]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Uncus relatively short compared with that of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,298,1429,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[183,298,1429,1454]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; distal part of uncus subapically rather high; tegumen very long, about 
<number box="[1139,1153,1429,1455]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
time longer than vinculum; saccus very short, V-shaped; juxta anchor-shaped; valva rather wide, relatively much wider and somewhat shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[389,504,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[389,504,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; harpe narrow, finger-like, parallel with margins of valva, situated more distally then in 
<taxonomicName box="[242,359,1549,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[242,359,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; aedeagus long and rather wide; shape of the everted vesica very different from that 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">L. ludicra</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, with multiple moderate and large diverticula, few of them long and broad, main part of vesica corpus and longest diverticulum finely scobinated. Carina without small dentate plate as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1259,1629,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[1143,1259,1629,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[222,311,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="6.[151,269,961,985]" captionTargetBox="[199,1404,156,900]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1405,156,915]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lygephila sp., female genitalia. 17, L. stueningi, paratype, genit. prep. 5883 M. Fibiger; 18, L. ludicra, Mongolia, genit. prep. C 21 B. Goater; 19, L. maxima, Russian Far East, Primorye Territory, genit. prep. 5725 M. Fibiger; 20, L. longicoecum, paratype, China, IBSS genit. prep. 698 V. Kononenko." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[279,311,1669,1695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Ovipositor lobes broadly triangular, setose; apophyses posteriores somewhat longer than anteriores and narrow, stick-like; ostium wide; antrum long, but much shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1211,1709,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[1097,1211,1709,1734]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, V-shaped, heavily sclerotised; ductus bursae very short, cylindrical; corpus bursae super-elliptic (that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1292,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[1174,1292,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="20">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is elongate, broadest posteriorly).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184113/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" targetBox="[151,1436,194,1787]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1847,1940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,1847,1871]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">FIGURES 1–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[328,434,1848,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[328,434,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Lygephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., adults. 1, 
<taxonomicName box="[586,712,1848,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stueningi">
<emphasis box="[586,712,1848,1871]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">L. stueningi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, holotype, China; 2, 3, ditto, female, paratype; China; 4, ditto, male paratype, China; 5, 6, 
<taxonomicName box="[453,560,1883,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludicra">
<emphasis box="[453,560,1883,1906]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">L. ludicra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Russia, Tuva, female and male; 7, 
<taxonomicName box="[952,1118,1883,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicoecum">
<emphasis box="[952,1118,1883,1906]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">L. longicoecum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, holotype, China; 8, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lygephila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">L. maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, Russia, Khabarovsk.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,418]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
